Create a Data Stream from a Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Extension

Create a data stream in Data Cloud, to ingest data from a Marketing Cloud Engagement data extension.

The frequency of data extension extracts is automatically defined, and you can’t edit it. Delta extracts are retrieved by

Engagement

hourly and processed hourly. Full Refresh extracts are retrieved by

Engagement

once daily. Since Data Cloud checks for files to process hourly, you’ll see 24 data stream refreshes but only one extract is processed. The rest of the extracts have zero rows processed due to no new data from

Engagement

.

In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab, and click New.
Select the Marketing Cloud data source, and click Next.
Choose a data extension.

A data extension can belong to one or more business units. Data extensions that belong to multiple business units are listed under Shared Data Extensions.

Select a business unit in the context filter drop-down to view its data extensions.
Select the data extension to import.
(Optional) Change the object label or object API name.
Select the category and define the primary key.
Review the field list, and optionally edit the field label, field API name, and data type.
(Optional) To cleanse your source data or get new fields, add formula fields.
Configure the data stream name, extract mode, and refresh mode.

If the data extension was already extracted from Engagement, the extract mode and the refresh mode are unavailable. Deleting and recreating the stream doesn’t enable these modes. To extract data using a different method, create a data extension with a unique name to use with the new data stream.

NOTE If a number or date data type field doesn’t exist in the data extension that you selected, the delta extract options are listed in the Data Extension Extract Mode drop-down.
Click Deploy.
To map the data source object to the data model, go to the Data Streams home page and click Start Data Mapping.

When the data extension is extracted for the first time, it takes up to 24 hours for data to be available in the system. After the first 24 hours, data is populated according to the frequency indicated in the data stream settings. Delta extracts load the previous 90 days of data when the data stream is initially configured. Subsequent runs load only new or updated records.

Data Extensions
Data Extension is a table within the application database that contains your data. You can use the data to run queries, pull information, and send to a subset of subscribers. Data extensions can be used in Marketing Cloud Engagement connector. Import Engagement Data Extensions into Data Cloud using our Engagement connector.
Extract Mode for a Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Extension in Data Cloud
Marketing Cloud Engagement Connector Extract mode dictates how Data Cloud exports and imports data from Marketing Cloud Engagement.
